  {
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I say this without any direct experience in minecraft, but it does seem like the system provides an environment that is both *tangible* and *live*. Maybe the constraint aspect is related to tangibility? (i.e. anything tangible must not be too flexible or vague/abstract, so must have more constraints, e.g. physical world based constraints?)",
    "user": "U8A5MS6R1",
    "ts": "1528507310.000052",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
